The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank matrix from corrupted entries, which is a common problem in machine learning and signal processing. The use of convex optimization and simulations suggests that the paper is likely to be in the machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
